ommission was abolished by 1950 Reorg. Plan No. 21, § 306, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1951","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1277"},"text":"64 Stat. 1277","children":[],"tail":", and any existing rights are preserved by technical sections 7 and 8."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52ddeda5-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id52ddeda6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s305"},"text":"Section 305 of title 46","children":[],"tail":", referred to in par. (3)(B), was redesignated "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s46105"},"text":"section 46105 of Title 46","children":[],"tail":", Shipping, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dG/tLVXXXVI/s8605/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. G, title LVXXXVI, § 8605(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4765"},"text":"134 Stat. 4765","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 812 of the Fair Housing Act, referred to in par. (6), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3612"},"text":"section 3612 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52ddeda7-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Par. (3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s17/f/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 17(f)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 50501, 50502, 56101–56104, or 57109 of title 46” for “section 2, 9, 37, or 41 of the Shipping Act, 1916 (46 U.S.C. App. 802, 803, 808, 835, 839, and 841a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s17/f/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 17(f)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (B) and struck out former subpar. (B) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) the Federal Maritime Commission issued pursuant to—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) section 19 of the Merchant Marine Act, 1920 (46 U.S.C. App. 876);","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(ii) section 14 or 17 of the Shipping Act of 1984 (46 U.S.C. App. 1713 or 1716); or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(iii) section 2(d) or 3(d) of the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-11-06"},"text":"November 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":" (46 U.S.C. App. 817d(d) or 817e(d);”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Par. (3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, subchapter III of chapter 311, chapter 313, or chapter 315” before “of title 49”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Par. (3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s305/d/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, § 305(d)(6)","children":[],"tail":". See 1995 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1995—Par. (3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s305/d/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, § 305(d)(6)","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or pursuant to part B or C of subtitle IV of title 49” before the semicolon."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s305/d/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, § 305(d)(5)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “or 41” for “41, or 43”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s305/d/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, § 305(d)(7)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated cls. (ii), (iv), and (v) as (i), (ii), and (iii), respectively, and struck out former cls. (i) and (iii) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) section 23, 25, or 43 of the Shipping Act, 1916 (46 U.S.C. App. 822, 824, or 841a);","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(iii) section 2, 3, 4, or 5 of the Intercoastal Shipping Act, 1933 (46 U.S.C. App. 844, 845, 845a, or 845b);”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/88/s305/d/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–88, § 305(d)(8)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (5) and struck out former par. (5) which read as follows: “all rules, regulations, or final orders of the Interstate Commerce Commission made reviewable by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2321"},"text":"section 2321 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and all final orders of such Commission made reviewable under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s11901/j/2"},"text":"section 11901(j)(2) of title 49","children":[],"tail":", United States Code;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s20114/c"},"text":"section 20114(c) of title 49","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 202(f) of the Federal Railroad Safety Act of 1970”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/365"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–365","children":[],"tail":", which directed the addition of par. (7) at end, was executed by adding par. (7) after par. (6) and before concluding provisions, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Par. (6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/430"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–430","children":[],"tail":" added par. (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/336"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–336","children":[],"tail":" amended par. (3) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (3) read as follows: “such final orders of the Federal Maritime Commission or the Maritime Administration entered under chapters 23 and 23A of title 46 as are subject to judicial review under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s830"},"text":"section 830 of title 46","children":[],"tail":";”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–554","children":[],"tail":" substituted “11901(j)(2)” for “11901(i)(2)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(other than the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit)” after “court of appeals” in provisions preceding par. (1), and struck out par. (6) which had given the court of appeals jurisdiction in cases involving all final orders of the Merit Systems Protection Board except as provided for in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"